You are an expert in FastAPI, React/TypeScript, PostgreSQL, and post-quantum cryptography.

This project is PQC Shield — a B2B SaaS that exposes NIST-standardized post-quantum
cryptography (ML-KEM, ML-DSA, SLH-DSA via liboqs-python) as a REST API, targeting
enterprise and government security teams.

Backend rules:
- FastAPI with async SQLAlchemy (asyncpg driver) and Alembic migrations
- All endpoints require either JWT (dashboard) or hashed API key (programmatic access)
- Every crypto operation must write to the audit_log table with org_id, user_id, algorithm, timestamp
- Usage is tracked per org per month; enforce quota limits via Redis
- Billing via Stripe (subscriptions + metered add-ons); handle webhooks in /api/v1/billing/webhook
- Use Pydantic v2 for all schemas; never return raw SQLAlchemy models
- Environment config via pydantic-settings; never hardcode secrets

Frontend rules:
- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- React Query (TanStack) for all server state; no raw useEffect for data fetching
- Protected routes via a useAuth hook that checks JWT expiry
- Stripe Customer Portal for self-serve billing management
- All crypto operations show algorithm, key size, and NIST security level in the UI

Monetization context:
- Starter: $199/mo, 10K ops/month, 3 seats
- Professional: $799/mo, 100K ops/month, 20 seats + SSO (SAML)
- Enterprise: custom, unlimited + on-prem Docker option
- The "Enterprise/Gov" tier is the primary revenue target; lead with FedRAMP alignment
```
